spirit:component.spirit:description: The GMII to RGMII LogiCORE(TM) creates a version 2.0 Reduced Gigabit Media Independent Interface (RGMII v2.0) by instantiating Input/Output buffers and Input/Output double data rate (DDR) flip-flops as required. This interface is used to connect the Ethernet MAC to an external Ethernet PHY. This module routes the rgmii_rxc from the phy chip (via a bufg) onto the rx_clk line. For S6 a DCM is used to shift the input clock to ensure that the set-up and hold times are observed. For V6 a BUFIO/BUFR combination is used for the input clock to allow the use of IODELAYs on the DATA.
